Key Match Events: Ali Sowe scored for Gambia in the 14th minute.
Abdi scored for Tunisia in the 11th minute.
Ali Ben Romdhane scored for Tunisia in the 76th minute.
Ferjani Sassi scored the match-winner for Tunisia in the 90+7th minute.
Pre-Game Insights: Gambia are currently in second place in Group A with one point, while Tunisia lead the group after beating Madagascar at home on matchday one of the competition.
Gambia are hoping to reach the Africa Cup of Nations main draw for a third consecutive time.
Tunisia, under the guidance of Faouzi Benzarti, made a positive start to their AFCON qualification campaign by beating Madagascar 1-0.
